To implement a generic resource struct or function in Go, we can create a type that has methods for different CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations. Here's an example of how you can implement it:

```go
// Define a type with generics for a resource
type Resource[T any] struct {
    id   int
    data T
}

// Define methods for CRUD operations on a resource
func (r *Resource[T]) Get(id int) T {
    if r.id == id {
        return r.data
    }
    return T{} // Return an empty value for the type
}

func (r *Resource[T]) Create(data T) T {
    r.id++
    r.data = data
    return r.data
