Here's a simple method in C# to check if a string is a palindrome:

```csharp
public static bool IsPalindrome(string input)
{
    // Remove non-alphanumeric characters and convert to lower case
    var cleanedInput = new string(input
       .Where(c => char.IsLetterOrDigit(c))
       .ToArray());

    cleanedInput = cleanedInput.ToLower();

    // Compare the input with its reverse
    return cleanedInput == new string(cleanedInput.ToCharArray().Reverse().ToArray());
}
```

However, a more efficient way to implement this would be to compare characters from the start and end of the string, moving towards the center of the string. This way, we only need to check each character once.

Here's the improved method:

```csharp
public static bool IsPalindrome(string input)
{
    var cleanedInput = new string(input
       .Where(c => char.IsLetterOrDigit(c))
       .ToArray());

    cleanedInput = cleanedInput.ToLower();

    int start = 0;
    int end = cleanedInput.Length - 1;

    while (start < end)
    {
        if (cleanedInput[start]!= cleanedInput[end])
        {
            return false;
        }

        start++;
        end--;
    }

    return true;
}
```

You can use this method in your C# program like this:

```csharp
public class Program
{
    public static void Main()
    {
        Console.WriteLine(IsPalindrome("Radar"));  // Outputs: True
        Console.WriteLine(IsPalindrome("Hello")); // Outputs: False
    }
}
```

The existing solution already ignores any non-alphanumeric characters. It uses the `Where` method and a lambda expression to filter out any characters that are not letters or digits.

However, if you want to make it clear that non-alphanumeric characters are being ignored, you could add some comments to the code:

```csharp
public static bool IsPalindrome(string input)
{
    // Remove non-alphanumeric characters and convert to lower case
    var cleanedInput = new string(input
      .Where(c => char.IsLetterOrDigit(c))
      .ToArray());

    cleanedInput = cleanedInput.ToLower();

    // Compare the input with its reverse
    return cleanedInput == new string(cleanedInput.ToCharArray().Reverse().ToArray());
}
```

Alternatively, you could use a regular expression to clean the input:

```csharp
public static bool IsPalindrome(string input)
{
    // Remove non-alphanumeric characters and convert to lower case
    var cleanedInput = Regex.Replace(input, @"[^a-zA-Z0-9]", "").ToLower();

    // Compare the input with its reverse
    return cleanedInput == new string(cleanedInput.ToCharArray().Reverse().ToArray());
}
```

This code uses the `Regex.Replace` method to replace any non-alphanumeric characters with an empty string, effectively removing them. The regular expression `[^a-zA-Z0-9]` matches any character that is not a letter or a digit.

