```

This might work, but it's not guaranteed, as the behavior can vary between browsers.

2. You can also try setting the `WebkitFullScreen` property to `hidden` when the browser is mobile-friendly:

```jsx
if (isTabletOrMobile()) {
  document.querySelector('video').style.WebkitFullScreen = 'hidden';
}
```

This will prevent the player from entering fullscreen mode, but it might affect other parts of your application.

3. Another approach is to add the following script tag to your HTML:

```html
